歪んだ面持ち、戯れる影法師
嗤うかぼちゃ、狐の仮面被り
夜霧のステージで踊る伝承の宴

18-18.title: Text-to-speech Models Suck
18-18.lyrics:
[Audience cheers]
Okay, okay...
Okay, so you know how there's all this buzz around A.I. voice generation?
Like, text-to-speech, voice cloning, yada yada yada...
And all those apps coming out telling you that
[sarcastic tone] "we got the most realistic one".
[Audience laughs]
I don't think I'm gonna have to drop names here, you know which ones I'm talking about.
[Audience laughs]
You know who's NOT telling you they have the best text-to-speech?
Udio.
And I know what you're gonna say,
"hey Kenny, that's not a text-to-speech model".
[Audience laughs]
[firmly] Yes it is.
[Audience cheers]
It is a text-to-speech model, if you WANT it to be.
And if you don't mind the whole "audience laughing in the background" stuff
[Audience laughs]
Exactly.
But I'm not even kidding, it's PHENOMENAL.
People tell me "wow, Kenny, did you try out the new Eleven Labs text-to-speech model?"
Oh, oops, there went the name-drop anyway I guess.
[Audience laughs]
And yeah, I play around with it for three seconds and am immediately bored.
[Audience laughs]
[yelling] CAUSE IT CAN'T YELL WHEN I WANT IT TO.
It just refuses to do emotion.
Nothing realistic about that, if you ask me.
[Audience cheers]
And then you find this random model that generates music.
And it's like "wow, so A.I. can do emotions after all".
So yeah,
apparently a random music model does text-to-speech better
than the best text-to-speech model.
[Audience laughs]
What kinda timeline is this?
[Audience cheers]

90-18.title: Tales by the Pond
90-18.lyrics:
[Verse]
In the early morning's hush, Bridget sets the pace,
With a babe cradled right, and milk jug in her embrace.
She passes by the gate where stories come alive,
Narrating past summers where memories thrive.
[Pre-Chorus]
"Last summer here," her gentle voice caresses the tale,
"A girl so small, with joy she would regale.
With parents close, this nook they brightly filled,
Their mirth like sunlight, the farm's air stilled."
[Chorus]
Beneath the oaks, they'd dance, near the pond's gentle sway,
Father's bright eyes gleaming, in the summer's soft array.
Ducks glide on water, chickens near them play,
And the turkey, in its folly, would gambol and bray.
[Verse]
With a spade, her father shaped a stream to pond,
Crafting a haven for the ducks to fondly bond.
From sadness to joy, their spirits freely cast,
In bread crumb waves, echoing laughter of the past.
[Pre-Chorus]
Morning's light would sparkle, bread soared in arcs high,
Pigs from the pen watching, beneath the wide sky.
Such simple pleasures, their days gently wrapped,
In warmth and care, their joyful hearts mapped.
[Chorus]
Beneath the oaks, they'd dance, near the pond's gentle sway,
Father's bright eyes gleaming, in the summer's soft array.
Ducks glide on water, chickens near them play,
And the turkey, in its folly, would gambol and bray.
[Bridge]
Yet time shifts, the pond now gone, to a ditch reclaimed,
Memories persist, love's imprint firmly framed.
Scenes transform, yet their love remains embraced,
In every heart touched, indelibly traced.
[Verse]
Now Bridget recounts, each step laden with tales,
Of summers spent where joy prevails.
Through her narrative's thread, past and present fuse,
Echoing love’s legacy, which time cannot defuse.
[Outro]
Hark, little one, to the tales of yore,
Where love melds with laughter, forever to explore.
Let these stories guide you, as through life you sway,
In hearts forever held, where they'll eternally stay.
[Chorus]
Beneath the oaks, they'd dance, near the pond's gentle sway,
Father's bright eyes gleaming, in the summer's soft array.
Ducks glide on water, chickens near them play,
And the turkey, in its folly, would gambol and bray.

[Instrumental]
[Verse]

Each stop's a tale of time, in silence to confide
[Bridge]

Tracing every line that life has thrown my way
Whispers of the past, a soft and subtle sign
Leaving marks as deep as tracks along the line
[Verse]

Together we are apart, surfing through the lines

As the tracks connect with life, we follow the same path.

In the company of shadows, every soul begins to rhyme

126-18.title: What am I doing with my life?
126-18.lyrics:
So what's the deal with skibidi toilet? It's a guy in a toilet. He's singing and running around causing trouble, defying all the laws of physics. And he has MILLIONS of views on YouTube. MILLIONS. A guy... In a toilet.... What am I even... Doing with my life?
And then the other day someone told me that I have... No rizz... What is that? Rizz... Sounds like a laundry detergent from the 1980s. "Use rizz to make your laundry so attractive!" 
No but seriously, did you know that the word "rizz" comes from the word charisma?!  So some kids on Omegle apparently were too lazy to have actual charisma, so they shortened... And misspelled the word into rizz. A four letter word. 
So that got me thinking... What other words could be shortened to something lazy kids could use? How about... Hippopotamus! We could shorten it to... Hipo. H.I.P.O. and how would we use this new word in a sentence you ask? Well, I'm so glad you asked!
H.I.p.O is used like this:
Definition: A chill, laid-back vibe. “He’s got that hipo energy.”
Example: “Let’s keep it hipo tonight—no stress!”

Now who has the Rizz baby? I've got that hippo Rizz...
So how about another new word? 
“Incomprehensible”:
Misspelled: “Inko” I.N.K.O. (that's right, inko.)
Definition: Something so wild or confusing that it’s hard to grasp. “skibidi toilet is totally inko.”
Example: “The plot twist in that Mike Tyson vs Jake Paul fight was totally... INKO..."

126-18.title: Aria
126-18.lyrics:
In her eyes, an abyss lies
Her solitude, no alibis
She traces back through time and pain
A life that fell like autumn rain
With every harmony so tight
She breaks away from endless night
In shadow's hold, her voice unfolds
A melody so dark, so cold
With every note, she bares her soul
In echoes that the night has stole
Beneath her gaze, the silence weaves
A tapestry of lost reprieves
Through the storm, her heart ignites
A force within that bravely fights
And in this song, her spirit soars
Her chains released, her soul implores
[Chorus]
Rise, rise against the dying light
Embrace the storm, the stars in sight
A revelation in her eyes (in her eyes)
The truth behind her thin disguise (thin disguise)
Ghosts of past that haunt her mind
Forbidden love she left behind
With every beat, her heart's parade
In the ashes her dreams remade
[Chorus]
Shatter, shatter the silence deep
Against the void, her solace seek
Heaven's tears in her eyes do speak
A revolution, bold and meek
Rise, rise like fire in the night
Claim the shadows, reclaim the light
[Bridge]
In the echo of the choir's lament
She finds the strength, she won't relent
Her revelation, stark and clear
In every breath, she conquers fear
[Outro]
So rise, rise like phoenix from the dark
In every ending, there's a start

Fights Andocrushers in the dead of night
Bobber growls, the showdown's near

From dark depths, her evil tells.

Hear my cry, O God;
    listen to my prayer.
From the ends of the earth I call to you,
    I call as my heart grows faint;
    lead me to the rock that is higher than I.
For you have been my refuge,
    a strong tower against the foe.
I long to dwell in your tent forever
    and take refuge in the shelter of your wings.
For you, God, have heard my vows;
    you have given me the heritage of those who fear your name.
Increase the days of the king’s life,
    his years for many generations.
May he be enthroned in God’s presence forever;
    appoint your love and faithfulness to protect him.
Then I will ever sing in praise of your name
    and fulfill my vows day after day.

324-18.title: The End of Eldorado for Stand-up Comedians
324-18.lyrics:
Have you ever wondered what the life of a person who writes stand-up comedy is like? Now imagine that this person is a computer. Yes, ChatGPT, our artificial friend trying to be funny. And I say "trying" because sometimes talking to it feels like debating with a very stubborn parrot that knows more words than just "fucker."
You start off: "Hey ChatGPT, write me something funny about my mother-in-law." And ChatGPT comes back with: "Sorry, but I cannot assist with content that might be considered offensive." Great, now the computer is giving me an ethics lesson.
And the best part is, ChatGPT tries to stick to the topic like a kid with a lollipop. You ask for a joke about politicians, and it'd rather tell you a story about how Abraham Lincoln bought a pair of jeans online. "Thanks, ChatGPT, now I know why history doesn't always have to be boring. But could it be somewhat relevant?"
But I must admit one thing: using ChatGPT to write stand-up has its perks. You don't have to worry about plagiarism lawsuits. Because who would have thought that the line "Sorry, I do not understand the question, but I can tell you about the history of the battle spear" was already in use somewhere?
So there you have it, folks, the future of comedy: safe jokes, stories that take turns you least expect, and a machine that stubbornly refuses to gossip about your mother-in-law. Doesn't that sound like the perfect evening?

450-18.title: Schwur der Helden
450-18.lyrics:
Der Namelose sinnt auf dunkle Macht,
mit dem Basiliskenkönig, in finstrer Nacht.
Aus den Schatten der Vergangenheit will er ihn erwecken,
Doch Helden stehen auf, um das Böse niederzustrecken
Rondril, der Ritter, von einfacher Gemüt,
Doch mit Herz aus Stahl, für Gerechtigkeit er blüht.
Sein Schwert führt er tapfer, ohne Zweifel und List,
Die Tugenden des Ritters, in seinem Herzen fest
Ludwig, der Schwerenöter, charmant und galant,
Mit einem Augenzwinkern, erobert er das Land.
Doch wenn die Not ruft, steht er zur Stell',
Mit Mut und List, gegen finstere Gesell'.
Anhe, die Kriegerin, mit magischer Klinge bewehrt,
Ihr Schlag durchdringt die Dunkelheit, nichts sie mehr begehrt.
Mit den Geistern der Ahnen, an ihrer Seite,
Blitzt ihre Klinge im Kampf, bereit für das Gute zu Streiten.
Arbogast der Zwerg, mit Armbrust und Geschick,
An der Seite seiner Freunde, im Kampf ein fester Blick.
Klein an Gestalt, doch groß im Herz und Mut,
Für Gut und Blut streitet er, mit Freude, voller Kampfeswut.
Eldarion, der Elf, mit Bogen und mit List,
Sein Pfeil durchschneidet Schatten, nie sein Ziel vermisst.
Mit alter Magie aus fernen Nebeln nah,
Er streitet für das Licht, gegen die Dunkelheit, klar und wahr.
Ashaybith die Magierin, geheimnisvoll und schön,
Mit ihren Zauberkünsten, lässt sie die Herzen fleh'n.
Verführerisch ihr Blick, mächtig ihre Hand,
Sie kämpft mit Magie, für das Gute im Land.
Gemeinsam schreiten sie voran, die Helden unverzagt,
Mit Mut im Herzen und Hoffnung, die niemals verblasst.
Für das Gute, das sie verteidigen, kämpfen sie Hand in Hand,
In einem Schwur vereint, für das Heimatland

468-18.title: Woven Land’s Heart: Down Under, Below (Smooth Soaring Mix) - Full Track
468-18.lyrics:
Under city’s lights where streets, brightly glow,
Cockatoos chatter, breaking lone night’s flow.
Secret painted laneway, train station’s plateau,
To cafes concealed - where only the locals go.
Sunrise avenues gleam - shadows grow slow,
Pause in a park to watch the day’s ebb and flow.
City’s rhythm, where dreams and hopes grow,
Brief rain, on pavement, the memories steps show.
Morning’s song - the sun’s horizon-blue beau,
Budgies rise and merge, life's transient throw,
Sleepy suburbs’ smiles reflect dawn’s fair go,
From high-rises tall and far out to greens below.
Beyond smoke’s edge, red ‘roos bound to and fro,
Dark bitumen trails dance under amber winds’ blow.
Night's tales spun 'round flames - embers aglow,
Tinnie in hand, us mates, planning tomorrow.
Warm hues in the bush - natural vast tableau,
Whole world on lamb-worn verandah to stow.
All from bustling lanes to outback window,
Life’s threads - my heart beats - down under, below.
In dawn’s warm light and cool breeze of night’s shadow,
Mending broken bonds - a new 'straya we'll sew.
With every city’s flare and outback’s bright glow,
A woven land’s heart resounds - in every echo.
Our free voices give rise to a form we know.
The pulse of which - we shall never let go:
To mates - all mates - we’ve us mates to bestow.
We're one. We're 'straya. We're the vibe, y’know?

486-18.title: Carrollton 1988
486-18.lyrics:
[Spoken]
On a stretch of road
That knew only the hum of passing lights.
A night unfolded in fury.
Wheels set against the wrong direction.
A bus.
A beacon.
Returning the weary.
Young at heart
Homebound from laughter
And thrill of fleeting escapes

[Intense]
[Shouted]
Headlights.
A harbinger in the dark.
An echo of laughter drowned in a sudden, stark glow of impending doom.
Metal clashed with metal.
Innocence met with reckless abandon.
Fire took the outlines of dreams.
And silence fell on screams.
[pre-chorus - intense]
Each flame carried a name.

Each spark a story untold.

The road - a pyre.
The night sky choked.
With the black smoke of despair.
[Chorus - melodic, rising intensity]

Remember them.
In the glow of flames.
Not as shadows lost to fire’s embrace.
But as lives.
That burned brighter than their end.
In the warmth of memories.
In the tears we shed.
[Spoken}
Survivors!
Witnesses!
Carries of scars.
Seen and unseen.
Bearers of burdens.
Their hearts a ledger of what should never have been.
Justice.
A word too frail.
To pale to cloak their pain.
What solace in survival?
When so many names are called in vain?

[musical interlude]



[Bridge - quiet, reflective]
Can forgiveness find its way through the smoke?
Can we reclaim peace from the ashes?
Or do we forever walk this road
Every step an echo of that night?


[Spoken]
In the hush that follows the fire.
Ash and charred remains.
Let there be a voice that speaks of them.
Not of the tragedy.
But of the spaces they filled.
Alive and vibrant.

[builds]
[Outro - intense]
For each life taken.

Let a thousand memories rise.

Above the flames.
Beyond the pain.

Into the clear and quiet skies

[end]

絶え間なき夢 (夢)
狂おしい速さで心は駆け抜け
断ち切れぬ思い、繋がるコードに
疾走する鼓動 (鼓動)
叫び出すリフ、炎上するリズムに
世界を変える旋律、永遠(とわ)のエコー
星空の下で (深い闇を越え)
刃のような風、断ち切る意志
加速する時、重なるビート
[ブリッジ: 彼女と, みんな]
痛みも喜びも (全てを抱きしめて)
織り成すメロディー、魂の共鳴
涙の先に (光を信じて)
鋼の意志で (意志で)
燃やすこの心、限界を超えて
翼は風切り、天に昇る
[Chorus: 彼女]
飛び立つ夢 (飛び立つ夢)
叫びを胸に、奏でるアンセム
絶望を裂き、希望を掴む
[アウトロ: 彼女]
星たちより (輝く夢を)
熱く燃ゆる声、空を貫く
希望へと (未来へと)
終わらない歌、光を纏って
切り拓く道、永遠(とわ)の煌めきに
[終曲]
今、飛び立つ夢 (夢)
